title: For Sale:  NEW - CSA SA vz. 61m .380ACP, 2 mags
postcontent: The .380 AUTO Sa vz. 61 Pistol is the semi-automatic version of the original 7.65mm Browning caliber Sa vz. 61 submachine gun. Czech Small Arms designed the .380 Sa vz. 61 to shoot SAAMI spec (American manufactured) ammunition (unlike the original 'Cold War' manufactured 7.65mm Browning vz. 61 that was developed using C.I.P. standards). CzechPoint has tested the .380 AUTO vz. 61s with a variety of ammunition and found common 'off the shelf' ammunition to exhibit outstanding reliability (examples: Federal, Winchester, American Eagle, etc). The original Sa vz. 61 submachine gun (machine pistol) was designed in the late 1950´s in Czechoslovakia and was intended for use with reconnaissance units, tank crews, Special Forces, and for security forces of the Ministry of Interior. The vz. 61 was developed to fulfill a specific need: a firearm that could be worn like a pistol (in a holster) and capable of full automatic fire. The 7.65mm Br. Sa vz.61 Pistol utilizes steel magazines and are drop free while the .380 AUTO Sa vz. 61 Pistol uses polycarbonate, TARFLON IR2500, and the magazines do not drop free from the lower receiver. Magazines purposely fit snug in the lower receiver for positive contact. Two 2nd generation waffle pattern magazines are included with the pistol. The design of the Sa vz. 61 was unique in its time. It uses the following common operational features found on a submachine gun: an unlocked bolt, magazine inserted into the bottom of the receiver (outside of the pistol grip) and a folding stock. These common features are combined with the following characteristics not usually found in submachine guns: extraordinary small size, fires from a closed bolt, and uses a rate reducer to slow full automatic fire. ATTENTION MARYLAND RESIDENTS: ALL PURCHASERS IN THE STATE OF MARYLAND ARE RESPONSIBLE FOR PROVIDING THEIR OWN MARYLAND APPROVED GUN LOCK. CZECHPOINT DOES NOT PROVIDE GUN LOCKS. Important Notes: * Our vz. 61 Pistol is a semi-automatic pistol and is not allowed by US law to have a folding stock unless the proper paperwork is completed and approved by the BATFE (all NFA rules apply). * The .380 AUTO vz. 61 Pistol does have drilled and tapped holes in the lower frame for attaching the folding stock mounting plate. * vz. 61 Pistols are assembled with original surplus parts that have seen military service. Czech Small Arms handpicks the best condition surplus parts from parts on hand and refnishes these parts. With that said, please keep in mind that these are used parts and they may exhibit dings and/or scratches under the new finish. * The vz. 61 design incorporates cocking knobs that slide against the upper receiver. For this reason, you WILL see scratches in the upper receiver paint when handcycling and/or shooting the pistol. postcontent: Up for sale is a USGI SpaceSaver Corp Universal Weapon Rack (UWR) - M110 Variant. This unit was stationed somewhere in Afghanistan and then flown back to Fort Bragg, NC. These cabinets were specifically used to store the Knights Armament M110 Semi Automatic Sniper System (M110 SASS). The US Army is replacing the M110 with a modified version of the G-28 from Heckler and Koch and has removed extra M110 storage cases no longer being used to make space. I recently completed a trip back down to Fort Bragg, NC to pick these up and bring them back to Virginia Beach, VA. They are in amazing shape. They have scratches from being moved around from plane to armory but NO RUST, NO DENTS, and NO BROKEN PIECES. Everything is in complete operational order. Many of you have seen me post various types of these cabinets but I have never had the M110 variant until now. Here are some great features:- All SpaceSaver UWR units meet both OPNAVINST 5530.13C and AR190-11 security requirements.- Fully welded construction with durable powder coating. - Cabinets can be ganged from the top, bottom, sides, or rear of other cabinets.- Bi-Fold retractable doors that prevent blocking aisles or neighboring racks and maximizes efficiency of the issuance of the weapons and gear. - Secure construction incorporating perforated doors, sides and back of cabinet to ensure visibility of items inside at all times. Great for doing inventory checks.- Retractable locking bars built inside of doors exceed military requirements for arms security of conventional arms, ammunitions and explosives. - All accessories that come into contact with the weapons are either powder-coated, vinyl dipped, rubber or thermoplastic-coated, or made from polymers to ensure that weapons are safe from damage in transportation. - This variant specifically includes an adjustable rifle butt stock holder. Made for aerial flight and transportation, it holds the rear of the rifle firmly in place. The butt plates are made out of plastic and will not scratch firearms. To adjust, just spin a wingnut and slide the holder on the track. - This variant specifically includes an adjustable rifle barrel holder that holds the barrel of the rifle in the rifle rack and keeps it from falling either direction. Heavy duty and is completely encased in vinyl and rubber to ensure your firearms are not scratched. This is adjustable as well, using a screwdriver, back the bolt out of the rack holder and the entire rifle barrel holder slides about 3-4" up or down for different barrel heights. - (1) M110 42.5"W x 61.5"H x 16"D Has room above rifle rack to put plate carriers, shelves, ect. - (4) M110 42.5"W x 45"H x 16"D Can be double stacked to save room.The item manifest that I received with cabinets shows that these cost between $1200-$1890 depending on configuration. I am listing the (1) 62" cabinet for $420 and the (4) 45" size cabinet for $380. I travel quite often and will deliver these directly to you for FREE. 50 Miles from 23462 is usually my limit however depending on quantity I can make further distances work.
